caption: I go to this great spot many times a year! This is the best place to pass a nice evening.  I visit this place routinely. The meals are of high quality, the crew is professional and the rates are good. I like eating in this place over a nice dinner.
One of my fav locations for delicious thai food. It was so fresh. The staff was helpful and kind. The bill was well within reason for the quality. Mood here reminds me of Colorado Springs area.
Crispy pork and rice

I think this is by far the best Thai place I have visited. This review is solely based on the variety, taste and price. I picked up food and cannot complain about any of those. The seating looks small, and the ambiance is not the greatest as well. But well, if you want to take Thai food home, then this is the place to take it from!

One of my favorite Thai places in the city. Flavors are always spot on for all dishes. Love their little kiosk they have set up for hot peppers, sauces, etc. The hot pepper flakes they have on the side is so fragrant and tasty. I also appreciate their water cooler, and hot tea in the winter, complimentary to customers.
Delicious food! We all enjoyed our dishes. And the mango sticky rice, divine.
Crispy chicken with anything is my go to!
If you stick to pad thai, it's an ok place, but everything else is just mediocre at best

Great for a quick bite if your in the area. Had the spring rolls, coconut soup with chicken, and pad Thai with peanut sauce on the side. All were very tasty and piping hot! Servers here are very patient and can offer insight and recommendations if prompted. Everything comes out lightning fast. The seating options here are not terribly expansive, but given the speed of the kitchen, spots free up quickly. Would recommend!
Delicious!
Ok place for Thai food. Great ambiance & decor. The service was very friendly and attentive. It has a cool feel to it. Mood here reminds me of Colorado Springs area.

The food is great and the service is always fast! I've eaten here 3 times in the past month and I have not been disappointed yet! The food is authentic and seasoned to your liking. I love spicy food, but I've gone with my friend who cannot stand any spice - and they make it just right for her! I highly recommend!
Simply the best Thai food in the Fenway backbay area. You won't be disappointed.  Cash only. they have a bathroom for patrons.
Food was very good and portions were substantial. Service was pleasant and quick. Real plates and utensils are a nice touch.
Delicious food. I especially love the crispy chicken pad Thai and the drunken noodles
Great value for great food
This is by far the best Thai cuisine restaurant I have ever ordered from. Fast delivery, inexpensive and utterly delicious! Very much recommend the Indonesian fried rice.
The food was poorly prepared. The plates smelled bad. I couldnt eat more that 2 bites and i had to through it away
The restaurant has great decor, atmosphere, and the staff are amazing.
Very oily, unhealthy, and gave me and friends food poisoning multiple times.

This place is awesome. Good food, very friendly staff. For the quality of food and service you get, this place is definitely not expensive at all. I try getting friends and family to come eat here with me any chance I get. I love you pho basil, stay awesome :)
Delicious and authentic!
Delicious food on the cheap! Very authentic as well.

Great food, consistent with other locations. Fast takeout. They give you a little container of hot sauce with each dish. Can't say enough good things, Rod Dee is the best! I love their Pad See Ew and spicy basil fried rice with pork.
Highly recommend getting the Indonesian fried rice!
My favorite Rod Dee location. Never been disappointed here. The quality to price ratio is favorable. Flavors on point. IMO best casual Thai food in Boston.

I love this place more than life itself. I have a job to support my diet of pad Thai but long for it when at work. Sad story really...  Pad Thai with crispy chicken (half spicy) and the Tom yum fried rice can't be beat.  CASH ONLY but they have one of them there ATMs on site. Well worth the convenience fee if you don't have any dough on hand.
I'm usually a drunken noodles guy, but here I always get the basil pad Thai.  Overall though, this place is a gem.  I wish it wasn't cash only, but not worth a star.
(Translated by Google) Inchia cioppu bellu!  (Original) Inchia cioppu beddu!
Yummy!
The place is decent but lost two star because they don’t take credit card. How arrogant it is to ask customers to go a mile to an ATM, calculate the price they would order to eat here.
Cash only
Great food, but cash only so make sure to bring the paper.
Great price
Best Thai food around! Pad kra pao is too good! #vegetarianfriendly #eatoutside #healthy
They are accepting only cash. It’s hard to pay cash for ten people. Food is also not that great.

I've been to a lot of Pad Thai places and I believe the best balance of flavor, price, and satisfaction has to go to the Pad Thai that you get here in Rod-Dee 2. What sets the Pad Thai here is that most places I go, it's either that the taste of the Pad Thai is underwhelming, or that the Pad Thai filled me up too much. Rod-Dee 2 gives you a good balance of flavor and satisfaction. The food great, but I felt like the presentation could be a little better, but that's just me nit-picking.

This cozy little cash only joint seats 12-15 people and serves up some high quality Thai food at a good price. My wife and I shared the Thai salad, the fried pork with basil sauce, and the Pad Thai. The fried pork was really good - crispy with nice basil-y flavors and a nice amount of heat. The Pad Thai was excellent. The Thai salad was not entirely what I expected...I expected something more along the lines of a traditional Thai salad. What we got was giant hunks of iceberg lettuce with some veggies, eggs, and tofu covered in peanut dressing. I looked up at my wife with disappointing eyes, realizing that I should have inquired about the contents of said salad before I ordered. I took a bite only to find all my disappointment disappear. That tasty peanut dressing made it all ok. Then I realized that maybe it's a genius move to use that tasteless iceberg as a vehicle for getting that all that delicious peanut dressing into my mouth. Well played, Rod-Dee.  My takeaway from the evening? Excellent food, fantastic and friendly service, and larger-than-my-mouth sized hunks of iceberg lettuce for getting that peanut dressing into my face hole.

We came here a week after visiting Thailand and this was stellar. Pad see ew was delicious (recommend adding jalapeño or red spice available at the side). Indonesian fried rice was out of this world - plus, we have enough left for a second meal.
Consistently great food. More of a take away place than an eat-in place.

(Translated by Google) If you go to Prudential Center and Berklee College of Music on your left for five minutes, it's a very nice Thai food restaurant next to the sidewalk.  Even if you ordered anything, it is very tasty and highly recommended. When I missed white rice I got a vegetable green curry.  Here in New England and the eastern part it is a delicious shop! It is filled with customers but will not be kept waiting slowly eaten at the seat  Boots in jeans, down coat glove hat and thick eyed muffler Even if the cell phone does not touch outside It is a truly amazing shop in Boston every day's extreme cold. (^ ^) It is tasty and delicious.  (Original) プルデンシャルセンター そしてバークリー音楽学院を左手に五分進むと歩道横にあるのが本当に美味しいタイフードレストランががこちらのお店。  熱々で何をオーダしても美味しく大変オススメです。白米が恋しかった時はベジタブルグリーンカレーを頂きました。  ニューイングランドおよび東部ではこちらが断然美味しいお店です！お客様でいっぱいですが待たされることはなくゆっくり座席でたべれます  ジーンズにブーツイン、ダウンコート手袋帽子と分厚いマフラーに耳あて 携帯でさえ外では触らない 毎日の極寒のボストンでは本当に有難いお店です (^ ^) 涙出そうに美味しいです。
Food is really good, place is small inside but there are tables outside if you like eating in the cold. Cash only though.
Great food, comfy and nice
Mediocre food - green curry was bland, although the vegetables were plentiful. Counter service, cash only.
Good food in good portions. Tea too.
Favorite place for good food near Fenway!
This place is typically very good.  I recommend the Indonesia Fried Rice!  A star off for being a little inconsistent with portioning and meat quality, and not taking cards.
Quick Service, Food Tastes Good, Please clean your table when you leave. Its Boston!
The food was okay. No debit/credit card accepted on site. They is a sign that ask you to clean up after yourself.

Stopped by for lunch. Location is very close to Fenway. This place takes cash only, but there is an ATM inside the store. Got the pad see ew with seafood, definitely tasted a little on the fishy side. Great outdoor seating area close to other food options on the same street.
Great restaurant. Everytime I come here, I order a different dish. Each time, the dish is delicious and amazing! Eat here!
Amazing Thai food for cheap! I had delicious yellow curry and was able to order, eat, and get back to work nearby all during my lunch hour.

The Spicy Crispy Chicken has become my go-to dinner when I don't feel like cooking, but everything else I've ever had here is great as well. Tom Yum Noodle Soup is particularly good in the winter months.
The food is pretty solid, but can be hit or miss sometimes. Usually very quick service (~5 min) but most recently waited nearly 30 min.

Loved the curry chicken, crispy chicken and the beef with fried rice. Small and clean place. We went for dinner on day without a Red Sox game so parking was easy to find. Will come back here next time we visit Boston.
By far best Thai restaurant in the Boston area. Pad Thai, rad nar and tom yum are better then then most I've eaten in Thailand!
2 stars for food, 0 for service
Pad thai was ok. Too oily. Customer service rate 1of 5
Used to be a favorite place of mine. Quick service, friendly, convenient.
Cash only restaurant with delicious food

This is a hole it the wall thai place behind fenway and its one of the best places for authentic thai food. I loved everything here! I had the tom yum pad thai noodles and they were spicy, flavorful and filling. I also tried the basil fried rice which was good. The fried chive dumplings were a little oily and had a mild wasabi flavor.

This is the best, most authentic Thai food I have ever had.  The people who work at and own it are so nice, and the food is so high quality and very fairly priced!  I have lived in Boston for 15 years, and though I have moved to a different neighborhood, I always return to Rod Dee-- it remains my absolute favorite Thai restaurant in Boston!!
Can be awesome but sometimes can be kind of terrible.  Mostly solid.
Indonesian fried rice is my go to and is so good!

Really great food, nice portions, but it is very unsettling when you see the front counter staff tweezing the servers eyebrows at the front counter and then the server is grabbing plates to serve to diners and then goes back in to finish getting her eyebrows tweezed, still at the front counter in front of diners. Not worth going back for me.
Rating speaks for itself
Have never had a bad experience with the food. Everything else was neat enough for a simple self service Thai cafeteria-style restaurant.

Cheaper than thaitation in the same neighborhood. I only tried vegetarian dishes and I like pad thai and drunken noodles (their best dish), I don't like their curries. Friendly and quick, sometimes noisy
Good cheap food, large portions, and fast, but mine had a short black hair in it.

Very solid Thai here. A good blend of authentic and the classics. Great place for guilty pleasure takeout. Crispy chicken is the best in town here - a must try with the Massaman or Panang Curry of over Pad Thai
One of the best authentic thai food in boston!

I dabble in Thai food... meaning I order between the same 2 things at every Thai restaurant. This place has the best yellow curry and pad Thai compared to the other options in the area. Bummer that it’s cash only but it’s worth a trip to the ATM! ... and sometimes worth the ATM fee that they have in the restaurant.
One of the best Thai noodle in Boston
Pad kra pow—my daily 'bread'

Really flavorful pad Thai, black bean sauce, and curries. Friend loves their Tom Yum soup. At the register, if you order a vegetarian dish they often ask whether you care about fish sauce, which is excellent service and attention.
Really good food, no frills, cash only
One of my favorite places to get Thai food. Staff is nice too. Can be difficult to get a seat inside sometimes because it's crowded and small, but there are tables outside.

Very yummy place for lunch! Most cost-effective in this bleeding expensive area! Personal favorites: pineapple fried rice (with chicken and shrimp), Drunkard noodle with tofu (spicy), and Tom yum noodle soup with shrimp (very spicy)
Great local place to eat. seating is tight, Especially when games are going on.
Every dish I have had is excellent.  Love the outdoor picnic tables.
Super friendly staff, delicious dishes, and quickly prepared dishes make for a wonderful experience.
Had chicken tempura and chicken in Black bean sauce. Delicious!
Best pad thai I've ever had (including in Bangkok)!!
The pad tai here is to die for absolutely incredible.
My favorite address in Fenway! The Pad Thai is always good (as well as other dishes) and good portion for the price.

Tonight was my first time buying food from Rod-Dee 2 Thai Cuisine. I ordered the chicken and shrimp chicken fried rice and loved it! It was very tasty!  My bf ordered the R2 which is sautéed mushroom, ginger & onion spicy with chicken and brown rice and liked it. & ordered The crab ragoon as well. & it was ok!  a lil sweet but still tasty. I also ordered the fried Chicken wings. The chicken was cooked thoroughly but lack some flavor & seasoning is what's missing only but it was still ok. Would I return definitely yes! I like the location! &  look forward to trying out other dishes sometimes soon.
Space is little but food is good
This was a good place in the midst of other choices.
I always enjoy their food. But remember its cash only
I love this place! Super delicious, great price! A heads up, they are cash only. They have an atm, but best to come prepared if you want to avoid the transaction fee.
Great authentic amazing thai food at a cheap price.

(Translated by Google) Authentic Thai food by Thai people sitting outside the shop, good atmosphere (if the weather is good), price is OK, quantity, American size Thai people who miss our food are not disappointed. It's a little hard to miss with the massive lines at El Pelon next door, but Rod-Dee 2 is an excellent spot for anyone interested in authentic Thai cuisine. Good food an reasonable prices. Will definitely be returning!
Love the Indonesian fried rice with chicken!!! Portions and price are great for the flavor and overall quality. During the warmer months is great to sit outside on the benches.

Great food. Cash only place. Some outdoor seating. Great in the summer. If you want to get away from all the new construction and new restaurants, this is a good place. The business around there is what is left from the old Fenway neighborhood.

Indonesian Fried rice is the best value dish in Boston. ~$10 for one of the best meals you can have here. Cash only but everybody who works there is so nice. On a sunny weekend day it is crowded but outside seating is plenty.
Good options, good taste, generous portions and good prices.
Don't forget to bring cash. The have an atm just in case. Food is unbelievable.
Authentic, delicious northern Thai cuisine at a reasonable price. The small seating area fills up quickly during the lunch rush. Be aware it is cash payment only; there is an ATM on site with a fee.
No frills Thai place. Great food, reasonable cost

I gave 5 star for the service (VERY friendly staff), 3.5 star for the food (I am a big fan of Thai food, so I must say I have a high expectation toward Thai food) and 4 star for the location (located near the Red Sock's stadium).  The service from their staff was just off the chart. Each and everyone of them was just incredibly friendly and helpful :)
Cash only!
Great food fast
this restaurant is one of the reasons for me to rent a flat nearby

What can I say.... the best Thai restaurant around here and (in Boston) actually. They know how to cook "Authentic Thai" food unlike other Thai restaurants that pretend they offer Thai food which actually is just something else! Love this place so much and it will be my next go to place for sure.
Fantastic!!!
Large portions, extensive menu & good food.
Very good food at a reasonable price. Great for take out as the indoor dining room can get a bit busy. Cash only...
Delicious thai food in large portions and a very confusing large menu

Good food, but terrible service and rude staff!  I would have given them 5 stars for the experience if the waitress had been more careful and not burned my 7 month old by placing a steaming hot plate of curry right in front of her, easy to dip her hands into.  Also, when I asked her if they had hot water to heat up some baby food - but they don't. Then she had to verify if I had ordered before she could give me some water.  They also want you to pick up your own plates and put them in a bucket.  I knocked off two stars for the rude service and inconsideration, and one star for having to clear your own table. Which is part of the reason you go out to eat, next time they might even make you cook your own food!
This is the best Thai restaurant, ever! I moved to NYC 7 years ago, and still haven't found a place that's as great and affordable. Try the pad thai (obviously) or basil fried chicken. Amazing!
Good Food, Less seating tho, Great for a to go spot....

Very good food and super friendly service. Had tofu pad see you. The tofu was crispy but not dry, and the sauce was great. The seating is limited, but I found a seat at lunch hour, and turn around is pretty quick. Definitely coming back more often!
Great fast casual Thai food. Decor and ambiance are low frills but the food is well spiced and portioned. You get your money's worth and your taste buds will thank you!
The indoor seating is hard to come by. But the dishes are amazing here. Can't go wrong with the basil crispy pork.
Sizes are great for the price. I usually get the basil crispy pork or the chicken sweet and sour. Only reason I don't go more often is that they're cash only and I don't usually have cash.
I love Thai and its hard to find a good resturant, but when my coworkers recommended this place, I was overjoyed!! Their food is AMAZING.
Yummy food! Pretty authentic over here.
Bad experience. Quality of ingredients is low. Employees are not friendly. Service is terrible.
Good cheap Thai food near Fenway and Longwood. Haven't been disappointed yet

This is their local take out spot. It has a few seats which you can eat at but I prefer it for take out. The food I've had there is pretty standard but it's good and cheap so always a great choice. You usually don't have to wait long for it either which is perfect!
great authentic thai food, very affordable as well.
They made my favorite dish, which wasn't even on the menu. Thank you!

Ever since my first visit to one of the many Rod Dees, I've been a major fan.  This location is somewhat tucked away from everything but certainly not hard to find. Size-wise, not the biggest of the Rod Dees but potentially the fastest. I've never had to wait super long for my food to arrive. Massaman Curry, Pad See Ew, the Star Noodle, and Pad Thai are all delicious and have ample amounts of heat. If you have been to one Rod Dee than you can expect pretty much the same level of quality although I mean this in a good way.  Only negative is lack of condiments. I'm a big fan of having a variety of sauces on hand for my food but they only have three options: soy, sweet and sour, and sriracha. More options would be nice but that alone is not a reason to never come back. The food alone is worth always coming back for.

I love this corner neighborhood Thai restaurant. The food is great. The best menu items are on the Special Items section on their paper menu. The crispy chicken pad thai is definitely the best value on the menu. I also recommend the Pad Ka Na (Chinese broccoli stir fried with chicken) and pad see you.   The decor is clean and bright and the workers are nice. Cash only.
Awesome food
This seems quite original Thai food, very good priced. Rich choice of Cuisine. Excellent overall experience.
Excellent Thai food!  Amazing pad kra pao and crispy chicken.  Super fast service.  Very affordable.
BEST TAKE-OUT THAI IN THE CITY, HANDS DOWN!
LET'S BE GLAD THERE'S NEWSPAPER ALL OVER THE WINDOWS HERE.. AND THAT SOMEONE ELSE WILL BE OPENING A RESTAURANT THERE SOON.
